{
  "texts": [
    "Table 2, RARO consistently outperforms all verifier-free baselines across model scales.",
    "With the 1.5B model, we achieve 41.3% accuracy compared to 37.7% for the best baseline (RL-Logit), an improvement of 3.6%.",
    "This advantage grows with model size: at 3B, our method (49.1%) surpasses the best baseline (RL-Logit, 43.1%) by 6.0%, and at 7B, it reaches 57.5%, beating the best baseline (RL-Logit, 49.3%) by 8.2%.",
    "These results demonstrate that our adversarial learning framework provides a strong signal for reasoning that outperforms not only purely supervised approaches like SFT or Rationalization but also RL-based approaches like RL-Logit.",
    "Stable Training Dynamics."
  ]
}